                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The document seems to be an official letter. The words θεϲπίζω and θέϲπιϲμα have only appeared in those papyri referring to imperial constitutions.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">Written in a horizontal format along the ﬁbers. The document’s original size cannot be estimated. The roll in its last use may have consisted of only one sheet, but, as it had been reused for the account on the verso (80), it may originally have well been longer. Only one legible line is preserved on the recto. The hand of the best-preserved lines is a professional and grandiose upright cursive with some extra curves, preceded by at least three and a half lines in smaller writing, possibly by the same hand.</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates CLI</note>
